{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "mold", "icon": "VOP/mold", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Mold"], "extent": [59, 68]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Simulates anti-aliased mold."], "extent": [68, 105]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator simulates anti-aliased mold."], "extent": [105, 149]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["You will first generate a material that outputs a color, then pipe its\noutput into the Surface Color input of this operator."], "extent": [149, 275]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The Mold Threshold (", {"type": "code", "text": ["mthresh"]}, ") input controls the contribution of the\nrotting agents, and represents a good candidate for animation at the\nshader level if tied to a ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/parameter", "type": "link", "text": ["Parameter"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/parameter"}, " operator. The lower the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["mthresh"]}, "\nvalue, the greater the overall moldy area. To increase the percentage of\ncore mold in the overall moldy area, bump up the value of the Core Mold\nAmplifier (", {"type": "code", "text": ["coremult"]}, ") parameter."], "extent": [275, 685]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the Surface Position (", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, "), Normal Vector (", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, ") and Surface Color (", {"type": "code", "text": ["Cf"]}, ")\ninputs are not connected, the global variables by the same name will be\nused instead. Typically, you will use ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "type": "link", "text": ["Rest Position"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}, " or ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg", "type": "link", "text": ["UV Space Change"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg"}, "\nas inputs for ", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, ", and any operator that yields a lit color, such as\n", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/shinymetal", "type": "link", "text": ["Shiny Metal"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/shinymetal"}, " or ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/lighting", "type": "link", "text": ["Lighting Model"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/lighting"}, ", as inputs for ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Cf"]}, ". You will not need to\ntouch ", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, " unless you wish to apply additional displacement to the mold.\nIf you need to access the global variables directly, they are available\nfrom the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global"}, " operator."], "extent": [685, 1329]}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1329, 1338], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/banana", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/banana"}], "extent": [1338, 1362]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/cavities", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/cavities"}], "extent": [1362, 1388]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global"}], "extent": [1388, 1412]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/lighting", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/lighting"}], "extent": [1412, 1438]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/rust", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/rust"}], "extent": [1438, 1461]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Mold"], "summary": ["Simulates anti-aliased mold."]}